.TH SIMPLE_SHELL "Agosto 25,2023" Linux "USER MANUALS"
.SH NAME
Simple Shell - command language interpreter
.SH SYPNOSIS
#include "header_shell.h"
./hsh.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple shell is a limited implementation of commands and functionality

.SS PATH
It does not perform any direct action, it allows the execution of commands without specifying the full path of the executable.

.SS INVOCATION
.IP Interactive
The simple shell can be called by typing ./hsh.

.IP Non-interactive
The plain shell can also be called via a pipe (eg echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh).

.SS Command Execution
After breaking a command into words, if it results in a single command and an optional list of arguments, the following actions are taken.

/bin/ls

.IP [[flags]...[arguments]]
Counts the files in the current directory according to the flags provided by the user.

.SS SHELL BUILTIN COMMANDS
 exit -exits the plain shell and returns to the user's original shell
 env - prints environmental variables

.SH BUGS
NO known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Juan Rodriguez & Neischaly Ruidiaz
